		<div class="comment-body"><p>To me, this was a VERY frustrating episode.  </p>
<p>It seems like the guest was more interested in talking smack about survivalists, homesteaders, organic gardeners, dead guys we&#8217;ve never heard of, and even trying to talk down to Jack a few times, than give any cogent answers to Jack&#8217;s persistent and patient questioning.</p>
<p>Even when asked THREE different times what to do about gardens that were deficient of certain minerals, Mr. Solomon repeatedly went back to slandering those who used dolomite lime in magnesium-rich soil, or people who used lots of compost (the &#8220;Shit Method of Agriculture: SAMOA&#8221; &#8211; really?), or those who keep seed banks, or just homesteaders in general.</p>
<p>Good gosh, Mr. Solomon, you have all this knowledge, why don&#8217;t you just condescend to us peasant homesteaders from your fief in Tasmania and tell us WHAT THE HELL MINERALS TO PUT ON OUR GARDENS?</p>
<p>Sorry.  Compare the forthcoming style of Steven Harris to Mr. Solomon, and perhaps you&#8217;ll see why I&#8217;m so frustrated.</p>
<p>Jack, please find another guest to talk to us about mineral supplements for soil.   Someone who will tell us how things work, and not berate us as &#8220;SAMOA&#8221; practitioners.</p>
